workflow.name: Extract structured data from medical documents with Google Gemini AI
workflow.description:
## How it works
Transform medical documents into structured data using Google Gemini AI with enterprise-grade accuracy.

## Classifies document types (receipts, prescriptions, lab reports, clinical notes)
- Extracts text with 95%+ accuracy using advanced OCR
- Structures data according to medical taxonomy standards
- Supports multiple languages (English, Chinese, auto-detect)
- Tracks processing costs and quality metrics automatically

## Set up steps
### Prerequisites

Google Gemini API key (get from Google AI Studio)

### Quick setup

1. Import this workflow template
2. Configure Google Gemini API credentials in n8n
3. Test with a sample medical document URL
4. Deploy your webhook endpoint

### Usage
Send POST request to your webhook:
```json
{
  "image_url": "https://example.com/medical-receipt.jpg",
  "expected_type": "financial",
  "language_hint": "auto"
}
Get structured response:
json{
  "success": true,
  "result": {
    "documentType": "financial",
    "metadata": {
      "providerName": "Dr. Smith Clinic",
      "createdDate": "2025-01-06",
      "currency": "USD"
    },
    "content": {
      "amount": 150.00,
      "services": [...]
    },
    "quality_metrics": {
      "overall_confidence": 0.95
    }
  }
}
```

## Use cases
### Healthcare Organizations

- Medical billing automation - Process receipts and invoices automatically
- Insurance claim processing - Extract data from claim documents
- Clinical documentation - Digitize patient records and notes
- Data standardization - Consistent structured output format

### System Integrators

- EMR integration - Connect with existing healthcare systems
- Workflow automation - Reduce manual data entry by 90%
- Multi-language support - Handle international medical documents
- Quality assurance - Built-in confidence scoring and validation

## Supported Document Types

* Financial: Medical receipts, bills, insurance claims, invoices
* Clinical: Medical charts, progress notes, consultation reports
* Prescription: Prescriptions, medication lists, pharmacy records
* Administrative: Referrals, authorizations, patient registration
* Diagnostic: Lab reports, test results, screening reports
* Legal: Medical certificates, documentation forms

nodes.name: Webhook Input
nodes.notes:
Receives medical document analysis requests

Accepts JSON payload with:
‚Ä¢ image_url: URL to medical document image
‚Ä¢ expected_type: Document type hint (optional)
‚Ä¢ language_hint: Language detection hint (optional)

nodes.name: Parse Input
nodes.notes:
Validates and extracts input parameters

‚Ä¢ Extracts image URL from request body
‚Ä¢ Sets default values for optional parameters
‚Ä¢ Prepares data for image processing pipeline

nodes.name: Download Image
nodes.notes:
Downloads image from provided URL

‚Ä¢ Supports JPEG, PNG, WebP formats
‚Ä¢ Handles various hosting services
‚Ä¢ Returns binary data with metadata
‚Ä¢ Automatic MIME type detection

nodes.name: Extract to Base64
nodes.notes:
Converts binary image to base64 format

‚Ä¢ Extracts image data for AI processing
‚Ä¢ Preserves original binary for reference
‚Ä¢ Handles various image formats
‚Ä¢ Prepares data for Gemini API

nodes.name: Prepare for AI
nodes.notes:
Organizes data for AI processing

‚Ä¢ Extracts MIME type for proper API formatting
‚Ä¢ Combines image data with input parameters
‚Ä¢ Validates data completeness
‚Ä¢ Ready for Google Gemini processing

nodes.name: Gemini Classify Extract
nodes.notes:
Document classification and text extraction using Google Gemini 2.0 Flash

‚Ä¢ Classifies document into medical taxonomy categories
‚Ä¢ Extracts all visible text with high accuracy OCR
‚Ä¢ Detects multiple languages automatically
‚Ä¢ Provides quality assessment and confidence scores
‚Ä¢ Optimized for medical document processing

nodes.name: Parse AI Results
nodes.notes:
Processes Gemini classification results

‚Ä¢ Parses JSON response from Gemini API
‚Ä¢ Extracts document type and confidence scores
‚Ä¢ Validates classification results
‚Ä¢ Prepares data for structured extraction phase

nodes.name: Gemini Structure Data
nodes.notes:
Converts extracted text into structured medical data

‚Ä¢ Applies medical document taxonomy schema
‚Ä¢ Extracts specific fields based on document type
‚Ä¢ Ensures regulatory compliance formatting
‚Ä¢ Validates data completeness and accuracy
‚Ä¢ Generates comprehensive quality metrics

nodes.name: Finalize Track
nodes.notes:
Prepares final response with comprehensive metrics

‚Ä¢ Parses structured medical data from Gemini
‚Ä¢ Calculates total token usage for cost tracking
‚Ä¢ Adds processing metadata and timestamps
‚Ä¢ Compiles quality metrics and confidence scores
‚Ä¢ Ready for API response or further processing

nodes.name: API Response
nodes.notes:
Returns standardized JSON response

‚Ä¢ Structured medical document data
‚Ä¢ Quality metrics and confidence scores
‚Ä¢ Token usage for cost monitoring
‚Ä¢ Processing metadata for audit trails
‚Ä¢ RESTful API format for easy integration

# Technical Details

**AI Model:** Google Gemini 2.0 Flash
‚Ä¢ Optimized for document processing
‚Ä¢ Superior OCR accuracy
‚Ä¢ Multi-language support

**Requirements:**
‚Ä¢ Google Gemini API access
‚Ä¢ Internet connectivity

**Performance:**
‚Ä¢ 95%+ extraction accuracy
‚Ä¢ 2-5 second processing
‚Ä¢ Multiple image formats

# Quick Start

**Test in 3 steps:**
1. Import workflow
2. Add Gemini API credentials
3. Send test request

**Test request:**
```
POST /webhook/analyze-medical-document
{ "image_url": "your-image-url" }
```

**Customize:**
